Yeah, drawing ruts can suck, but I also let them fuel me to get better, too.
For practice I tend to make copies of drawings I like, usually with a focus on proportions and stuff. Say, I like how Krekkov draws a face, so I'll try to redraw it while paying attention to the distance between the eyes, where the eyeline falls on the face (while eyes are conventionally centered on real humans, some artists tend to drop them lower), etc.

Just drawing whatever goes a long way, though. I started drawing whatever fun/silly stuff I wanted for /sus/ a few years back and that helped moved me forward faster than anything else.
